- My mother bought me this shirt.</i>

575
01:01:05,591 --> 01:01:09,028
<i>- She has good taste.</i>
- I know.

576
01:01:29,710 --> 01:01:32,122
- No, wait.
- Are you okay?

577
01:02:11,157 --> 01:02:13,073
What is going on in here?

578
01:02:14,811 --> 01:02:16,648
You gonna hurt your ears,

579
01:02:17,173 --> 01:02:18,995
silly boy.

580
01:02:20,379 --> 01:02:22,404
Why did you do that for?

581
01:02:44,478 --> 01:02:46,209
...if you stayed
in town tonight.

582
01:02:46,589 --> 01:02:48,926
Okay. What just happened?

583
01:02:50,032 --> 01:02:51,469
That music...

584
01:02:51,954 --> 01:02:53,256
That was...

585
01:02:54,912 --> 01:02:56,528
Children have tantrums.

586
01:02:56,853 --> 01:02:58,187
It was a tantrum.

587
01:02:58,598 --> 01:03:01,017
Alright, I understand
what this means to you.

588
01:03:01,291 --> 01:03:03,884
But just step back for a
second, get some perspective.

589
01:03:03,886 --> 01:03:05,248
No, I don’t need perspective.

590
01:03:05,627 --> 01:03:08,930
<i>I know exactly what is happening
here and I am not going anywhere.</i>

591
01:03:09,367 --> 01:03:11,407
<i>The Heelshires ask me
to look after him.</i>

592
01:03:11,408 --> 01:03:13,224
<i>I promised the Heelshires
to take care of him.</i>

593
01:03:13,250 --> 01:03:15,811
<i>Under the circumstances I
think they will understand.</i>

594
01:03:15,986 --> 01:03:18,485
They chose me. They
want me to stay here.

595
01:03:18,945 --> 01:03:20,200
With Brahms.

596
01:03:30,476 --> 01:03:32,299
I should have told
you this before,

597
01:03:33,736 --> 01:03:35,574
but I didn’t want
to scare you off.

598
01:03:36,811 --> 01:03:39,034
A little girl from town
used to come out here,

599
01:03:39,159 --> 01:03:41,121
