- No, they never did.

609
01:04:07,023 --> 01:04:08,752
What I’m saying is, if
you’re right, if this...

610
01:04:08,753 --> 01:04:10,835
...thing is some kind of
spirit or ghost or...

611
01:04:11,363 --> 01:04:13,234
...hey, I don’t even know.

612
01:04:14,349 --> 01:04:16,155
I’m not sure....

613
01:04:16,680 --> 01:04:19,086
...that it is the good kind.

614
01:04:20,005 --> 01:04:22,402
Well, you said it yourself
that’s just pub talk.

615
01:04:22,604 --> 01:04:24,641
But what if it isn’t?

616
01:04:27,292 --> 01:04:29,508
I know he wouldn’t hurt me.
I know.

617
01:04:29,533 --> 01:04:31,748
It’s not safe in
this house, okay?

618
01:04:36,893 --> 01:04:38,534
I am not leaving.

619
01:04:41,975 --> 01:04:43,375
Okay.

620
01:04:45,200 --> 01:04:47,996
Now go straight to sleep
like a good boy, okey?

621
01:04:53,222 --> 01:04:55,324
You wouldn’t hurt me,
would you Brahms?

622
01:05:49,731 --> 01:05:51,587
<i>Emily Cribbs.</i>

623
01:06:30,412 --> 01:06:32,071
Who is hungry?

624
01:06:35,539 --> 01:06:36,814
I am.

625
01:06:43,038 --> 01:06:44,338
Malcolm?

626
01:06:48,870 --> 01:06:50,726
Let’s go to see.

627
01:06:53,500 --> 01:06:54,800
Malcolm?

628
01:06:55,125 --> 01:06:56,430
I thought...

629
01:07:02,536 --> 01:07:03,936
Cole?

630
01:07:04,861 --> 01:07:06,320
Who is Malcolm?

631
01:07:08,145 --> 01:07:10,316
I was going to write
you a letter, but,

632
01:07:10,741 --> 01:07:12,103
you know me.

633
01:07:12,634 --> 01:07:14,476
Never been one for writing.

634
01:07:15,050 --> 01:07:16,590
It’s the little fellow?

635
01:07:17,361 --> 01:07:18,912
What’s his name?

636
01:07:20,007 --> 01:07:21,368
Brahms.

637
01:07:28,931 --> 01:07:31,235
This is a joke, right?

638
01:07:34,662 --> 01:07:36,712
There isn’t a little boy.
They...

639
01:07:37,483 --> 01:07:39,664
They paid me to
look after a doll.

640
01:07:43,709 --> 01:07:45,176
You serious?

641
01:07:45,635 --> 01:07:48,631
Well, that makes things a
hell of a lot simpler.

642
01:07:49,041 --> 01:07:52,244
Whole way here I was trying to figure
out how I was going to convince you...

643
01:07:52,245 --> 01:07:55,759
...to come home and how we deal
with the boy, but now this shit.

644
01:07:59,390 --> 01:08:01,772
I’ve been working out
at Fairview with...

645
01:08:02,044 --> 01:08:03,414
...Ed Bruner’s crew.

646
01:08:03,738 --> 01:08:06,638
They got a contract on a...
on a new hotel.

647
01:08:07,216 --> 01:08:09,760
So there’s more enough
work for all of us.

648
01:08:10,651 --> 01:08:11,786
Well,

649
01:08:12,458 --> 01:08:14,638
that’s awesome, Cole.
Is what you wanted.

650
01:08:20,937 --> 01:08:22,357
I understand why you left.

651
01:08:22,682 --> 01:08:23,754
I do.

652
01:08:32,413 --> 01:08:34,253
Our flight leaves
tomorrow afternoon.

653
01:08:36,323 --> 01:08:38,887
- Taking you home.
<i>- Greta?</i>

654
01:08:41,884 --> 01:08:43,005
Oh sorry, I...

655
01:08:43,430 --> 01:08:45,589
- I let myself in.
- That’s okay, this is...

656
01:08:46,091 --> 01:08:47,437
- This is Malcolm. He brings our...
- Malcolm.

657
01:08:47,438 --> 01:08:49,055
...groceries and stuff out here.

658
01:08:49,056 --> 01:08:50,968
- Hey, nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you man.

659
01:08:52,471 --> 01:08:54,234
So what do you think
about all this...

660
01:08:54,659 --> 01:08:56,022
...doll stuff?

661
01:08:56,123 --> 01:08:59,397
You know, I try not to get involved
in other people’s business.

662
01:09:02,219 --> 01:09:03,377
Smart man.

663
01:09:04,248 --> 01:09:06,919
I have that delivery if you’d
like to go to the inventory list.

664
01:09:06,925 --> 01:09:07,963
Yeah, sure.

665
01:09:08,288 --> 01:09:09,370
I'll be right back.

666
01:09:21,601 --> 01:09:24,302
- What the hell is he doing here?
- He just showed up.

667
01:09:24,704 --> 01:09:27,412
Well, he has to leave. He can’t
ask you let him stay here.

668
01:09:27,413 --> 01:09:29,404
No, I don’t. I am not
letting him do anything.

669
01:09:30,080 --> 01:09:31,841
He wants me to go home with him.

670
01:09:31,866 --> 01:09:33,726
Well, that isn’t gonna happen.

671
01:09:37,590 --> 01:09:40,143
- And what if he attacks you?
- He won't.

672
01:09:40,668 --> 01:09:42,576
Trust me.

673
01:09:43,676 --> 01:09:45,130
